web-browser - Web Browser Launcher

USAGE:
    web-browser [-new-private-window] [-http-proxy=proxy] [-socks-proxy=proxy] [URL]

DESCRIPTION:
    Launch a web browser with specified URL and options.

ARGUMENTS:
    URL
        URL to open (optional)
        must be specified last due to how arguments are processed

OPTIONS:
    -new-private-window
        Create private window

    -http-proxy=proxy
        Address of HTTP proxy server

    -socks-proxy=proxy
        Address of SOCKS proxy server

    -remote-debug
        Enable remote control through Chrome DevTools Protocol

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-web-browser-browser BROWSER
        Browser to use (firefox/chromium)

    -web-browser-remote-debug 0|1
        Enable remote debugging

    -web-browser-http-proxy URL
        Default HTTP proxy

    -web-browser-socks-proxy URL
        Default SOCKS proxy

EXAMPLES:
    web-browser
    web-browser https://example.com
    web-browser -new-private-window
    web-browser -http-proxy=localhost:8080
